     9→/// Implementation of [SyncManager]
    10→///
    11→/// This implementation coordinates the synchronization process between
    12→/// local database and remote server. It ensures only one sync cycle runs
    13→/// at a time and automatically triggers sync when connectivity is restored.
    14→///
    15→/// The sync manager follows a phased approach:
    16→/// 1. **Upload Phase**: Sync queued local changes to server
    17→/// 2. **Download Phase**: Pull server changes to local database
    18→/// 3. **Conflict Resolution**: Resolve any conflicts
    19→/// 4. **Finalization**: Complete sync and update metadata
    20→///
    21→/// Note: Upload and download phases will be fully implemented in
    22→/// subsequent subtasks (5.2 and 5.3). This implementation provides
    23→/// the coordination framework and auto-sync triggers.
    24→class SyncManagerImpl implements SyncManager {
    25→  /// Connectivity service for network monitoring
